    <title type="text">Help sought with Metadata for the Open Patrologia Graeca Online</title>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://tinyurl.com/p39fx3f"><span style="font-family:
      inherit;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span
      id="docs-internal-guid-e8122189-0705-4248-5baf-a4bfab95eaf3" style="background-color:
      transparent; color: black; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Help sought with Metadata for the Open
      Patrologia Graeca Online</span></span></span></a><br /><div
      dir="ltr" id="docs-internal-guid-f3648d0b-0706-5aa0-68a0-480e569d365d" style="line-height:
      1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="background-color: transparent;
      color: black; font-family: Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal;
      font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">[draft -- January 19,
      2015]</span></div><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt;
      margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family:
      Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Gregory
      Crane</span></div><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt;
      margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family:
      Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Perseus Project and the Open Philology
      Project</span></div><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt;
      margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family:
      Arial; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">The University of Leipzig and Tufts
      University</span></div><blockquote class="tr_bq"><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><br /></span><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15;
      margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">We are looking for help in preparing metadata for the </span><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: italic;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">Patrologia Graeca </span><span style="background-color: transparent;
      color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight:
      normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">(PG) component of what we are
      calling the </span><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black;
      font-family: Arial; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Open Migne Project</span><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">, an attempt to make the most useful possible transcripts of the full Patrologia
      Graeca and Patrologia Latina freely available. Help can consist of proofreading, additional
      tagging, and checking the volume/column references to the actual PG. In particular, we would
      welcome seeing this data converted into a dynamic index into online copies of the PG in
      Archive.org, the HathiTrust, Google Books, or Europeana. For now, we make the working XML
      metadata document available on an as-is basis. </span></span></div><span
      style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span><div dir="ltr" style="line-height:
      1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">Nick White (normally at Durham in the UK but at the time at Tufts) trained and
      ran the Tesseract OCR engine and Bruce Robertson (Mount Allison University, Canada) the OCRopus
      OCR engine on scans of multiple copies of each volume of the Patrologia Graeca. The resulting
      OCR runs contain among them a very very high percentage of the correct readings and we will be
      able to support very useful searching, as well as text mining with this
      corpus.</span></span></div><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br
      /></span><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top:
      0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="background-color: transparent;
      color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight:
      normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">To support this larger effort, we
      are working on Metadata for the collection. We have OCRd and begun editing the core index at
      columns 13-114 of </span><a
      href="http://archive.org/details/PatrologiCursusCompletusAccuranteJ.-p.MigneseriesGrcaIndices"
      style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color:
      #1155cc; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline;">Cavallera’s 1912 index to the
      PG</span></a><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black;
      font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"> (which Roger Pearse cites at
      </span><a href="http://www.roger-pearse.com/weblog/patrologia-graeca-pg-pdfs/"
      style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color:
      #1155cc; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: underline; vertical-align:
      baseline;">http://www.roger-pearse.com/weblog/patrologia-graeca-pg-pdfs/</span></a><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">). A working TEI XML transcription, which has begun capturing the data within the
      print source, is available for inspection at: </span><a
      href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/mldhu4okpq4i7r8/pg_index2.xml" style="text-decoration:
      none;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color: #1155cc; font-family: Arial;
      font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: underline;
      vertical-align:
      baseline;">https://www.dropbox.com/s/mldhu4okpq4i7r8/pg_index2.xml</span></a><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">.</span></span></div><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><br /></span><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15;
      margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">This XML file will be used to expand the data in the Perseus Catalog
      (</span><a href="https://github.com/PerseusDL/catalog_data" style="text-decoration:
      none;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color: #1155cc; font-family: Arial;
      font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: underline;
      vertical-align:
      baseline;">https://github.com/PerseusDL/catalog_data</span></a><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">) and the coverage (as well as the rapidly evolving functionality) of the Perseus
      Catalog (</span><a href="http://catalog.perseus.org/" style="text-decoration:
      none;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color: #1155cc; font-family: Arial;
      font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: underline;
      vertical-align: baseline;">http://catalog.perseus.org/</span></a><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">). </span></span></div><span style="font-size:
      x-small;"><br /></span><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15;
      margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">All figures are preliminary and subject to modification (that is one motivation
      for posting this call for help), but we do not expect that the figures will change much at this
      point. At present, we have identified 658 authors and 4,287 works. The PG contains extensive
      introductions, essays, indices etc. and we have tried to separate these out by scanning for
      keywords (e.g., </span><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black;
      font-family: Arial; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">praefatio</span><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">, </span><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black;
      font-family: Arial; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">monitum</span><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">, </span><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black;
      font-family: Arial; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">notitia, index</span><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">). We estimate that there are 204,129 columns of source text and 21,369 columns
      of secondary sources, representing roughly 90% and 10% respectively. Since a column in Migne
      contains about 500 words and since the Greek texts (almost) always have accompanying Latin
      translations, the PG contains up to 50 million words of Greek text but many authors have
      extensive Latin notes and in some cases no Greek text. We will have better figures on the
      amount of Greek when we have analyzed the OCR-generated text for various copies of the
      PG.</span></span></div><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br
      /></span><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top:
      0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="background-color: transparent;
      color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight:
      normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">The PG was a vast enterprise that
      built upon centuries of work and cites c. 180 different editions, with work of
      </span><a href="http://viaf.org/viaf/46898988/" style="text-decoration:
      none;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color: #1155cc; font-family: Arial;
      font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: underline;
      vertical-align: baseline;">Andrea Gallandi </span></a><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">(1709-1779), </span><a href="http://viaf.org/viaf/100180720/"
      style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color:
      #1155cc; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline;">Angelo Mai
      </span></a><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black;
      font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">(1782-1854), </span><a
      href="http://viaf.org/viaf/7522175/" style="text-decoration: none;"><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: #1155cc; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align:
      baseline;">François Combefis</span></a><span style="background-color:
      transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal;
      font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"> (1605-1679),
      </span><a href="http://viaf.org/viaf/17330479/" style="text-decoration:
      none;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color: #1155cc; font-family: Arial;
      font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: underline;
      vertical-align: baseline;">Giovanni Domenico Mansi</span></a><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;"> (1692-1769), and </span><a href="http://viaf.org/viaf/56655251/"
      style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="background-color: transparent; color:
      #1155cc; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline;">Leo Allatius
      </span></a><span style="background-color: transparent; color: black;
      font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal;
      text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">(1586-1669) as the most frequently cited
      sources. </span></span></div><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br
      /></span><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top:
      0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="background-color: transparent;
      color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight:
      normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">We have focused on the following
      tasks. For details of the TEI XML tagging, you can consult the XML file:</span><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;"><br class="kix-line-break" /></span></span></div><ol
      style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt;"><li dir="ltr" style="background-color:
      transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal;
      font-weight: normal; list-style-type: decimal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;"><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top:
      0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="background-color: transparent;
      color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight:
      normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">We have provided VIAF IDs for many
      ancient authors and modern editors. </span></span></div></li><li
      dir="ltr" style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style:
      normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; list-style-type: decimal; text-decoration:
      none; vertical-align: baseline;"><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom:
      0pt; margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">Each author has been given its own ID# in the form of MPG + a 3 digit
      number.</span></span></div></li><li dir="ltr"
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; list-style-type: decimal; text-decoration: none;
      vertical-align: baseline;"><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt;
      margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="background-color:
      transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal;
      font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">We have tried to
      distinguish primary sources from the many secondary sources (commentaries, essays,
      introductions) that the PG contains. </span></span></div></li><li
      dir="ltr" style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style:
      normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; list-style-type: decimal; text-decoration:
      none; vertical-align: baseline;"><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom:
      0pt; margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align:
      baseline;">Each primary source has a work ID of the form MPG + a 4 digit number. Together
      with the author ID, these allow us to define URNs according to the Canonical Text Services/CITE
      Architecture.</span></span></div></li><li dir="ltr"
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; list-style-type: decimal; text-decoration: none;
      vertical-align: baseline;"><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt;
      margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="background-color:
      transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal;
      font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Secondary sources
      have an ID of the form SSID + 4 digits. Secondary sources are numbered sequentially through the
      PG index. The main goal here is to distinguish them from the original source
      texts.</span></span></div></li><li dir="ltr"
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; list-style-type: decimal; text-decoration: none;
      vertical-align: baseline;"><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt;
      margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="background-color:
      transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal;
      font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">The 56 editors whose
      names show up three or more times surrounded by parentheses haves been given a VIAF number and
      tagged.</span></span></div></li><li dir="ltr"
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; list-style-type: decimal; text-decoration: none;
      vertical-align: baseline;"><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt;
      margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="background-color:
      transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal;
      font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">The headers for each
      new author normally contain a date, most commonly the century of main activity recorded as a
      roman numeral but occasionally as an arabic number date range. We have tried to capture and
      encode these.</span></span></div></li><li dir="ltr"
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; list-style-type: decimal; text-decoration: none;
      vertical-align: baseline;"><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt;
      margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="background-color:
      transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal;
      font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">We have scanned for
      references in the form of “volume, column1-column2.” Where the index leaves out the volume
      number, we assume that we are still using the last recognized
      volume.</span></span></div></li><li dir="ltr"
      style="background-color: transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal;
      font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; list-style-type: decimal; text-decoration: none;
      vertical-align: baseline;"><div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0pt;
      margin-top: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="background-color:
      transparent; color: black; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal;
      font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">The index commonly
      truncates number ranges: e.g., 1235-54 instead of 1235-1254. We have tried to expand the
      truncated numbers and checked to make sure that the resulting ranges are increasing (e.g.,
      column2 does not occur before
      column1).</span></span></div></li></ol></blockquote><br
      />]]></content>
